        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-10-04T23:30:34.665Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"hs_h1\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"72042\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/hs_h1/48/54080_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> hs_h1:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>can easily view images just by scrolling through the chat room without touching the image group.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>You can also easily tap the image group once and scroll through the images. I feel like having to scroll past a long line of images would be annoying more often than it would be beneficial.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"hs_h1\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"72042\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/hs_h1/48/54080_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> hs_h1:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>since you can leave reactions and replies for each photo, it will be helpful for business when sharing multiple images.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Not sure what this has to do with businesses, but this could be addressed with a different approach:</p><aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"9058\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/meteor0id/48/55420_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/reply-forward-react-to-a-single-photo-out-of-a-group-of-photos-and-enhance-the-reply-message-bubble/9058\">Reply/forward/react to a single photo out of a group of photo's (and enhance the reply message bubble)</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Currently When I try to reply to a photo from a group there is no option for that. I can reply to the message which contains a group of photo‚Äôs. The reply preview will show the text ‚ÄúPhoto‚Äù which is incorrect because I am replying to a ‚Äúgroup of photo‚Äôs‚Äù (plural). Once I reply or forward a very small preview will be shown of only one of the images I replied to, again with the text ‚Äúphoto‚Äù. This may lead other to believe I am only replying to that particular photo, which is not true, I am replyin‚Ä¶\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
